# Alerting, Dashboard & Reporting — Person 5
### Amazon SNS + AWS Amplify + AWS Security Hub

---

## What This Layer Does

Person 5 is responsible for **delivering alerts to the team, building the visual dashboard, and coordinating the final report and presentation**. This is the user-facing output of the entire detection pipeline — when an attack is found, this layer notifies the team and displays it on a live dashboard.

---

## AWS Services Used

### Amazon SNS (Simple Notification Service)
SNS is a fully managed pub/sub messaging service. Publishers send messages to a topic; all subscribers receive it instantly.

**How it is used:**
- An **SNS topic** (`sql-injection-alerts`) receives messages from Lambda (Person 3) on HIGH or CRITICAL detections
- **All 5 team members** subscribe with their email addresses
- **Optional SMS** subscription sends text message alerts to a designated phone number
- Each notification includes:
  - Timestamp
  - Source IP address
  - Attack type (union-based, blind, error-based)
  - Severity level (HIGH / CRITICAL)
  - The exact SQL payload that triggered the detection

### AWS Amplify
Amplify is a full-stack platform for deploying web apps on AWS with built-in CI/CD from a Git repository.

**How it is used:**
- A **React web application** is built and deployed to Amplify as the live visual dashboard
- **Live attack feed:** Displays the 20 most recent detection events (pulled from DynamoDB, populated by Lambda)
- **Charts:**
  - Bar chart — attack type breakdown (union vs. blind vs. error-based)
  - Pie chart — blocked vs. unblocked request rates
  - World map — geographic distribution of source IPs
- **Security Hub score** embedded on the dashboard for at-a-glance security posture

### AWS Security Hub
Security Hub is a centralised security posture management service. It aggregates findings from GuardDuty, WAF, Inspector, and Config into one view.

**How it is used:**
- **Findings aggregation:** Ingests GuardDuty findings and Lambda-published findings in one console
- **Compliance scoring:** Evaluates the project against the **CIS AWS Foundations Benchmark** — produces a compliance percentage
- **Executive reporting:** The Security Hub summary provides the top-level security posture view for the final report
- **Normalised severity:** Displays GuardDuty and Lambda findings side by side with consistent severity labels

